# CURSOR PROJECT RULES — Jacob Shope Mortgage Website

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

You are building a professional mortgage loan officer website for **Captain Jacob Shope**, a Charlotte Fire Department captain and licensed mortgage loan officer (NMLS# 2090979) at Mpire Financial (NMLS# 2090979). The site serves the Charlotte, NC metro area (primary) and statewide North Carolina (secondary).

The site must be fast, mobile-first, SEO-optimized, and designed to generate mortgage leads. It should rank for local search terms in Charlotte and surrounding areas.

---

## TECH STACK (Do not deviate from this)

- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (utility-first, no custom CSS files unless absolutely necessary)
- **UI Components:** shadcn/ui (install components as needed via CLI)
- **Icons:** Lucide React
- **Charts:** Recharts (for mortgage calculators)
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod validation
- **SEO:** next-seo or Next.js built-in metadata API
- **Sitemap:** next-sitemap
- **Analytics:** Google Analytics 4 (via @next/third-parties or next/script)
- **Images:** Next.js `<Image>` component (always — never use `<img>`)
- **Font:** next/font with Inter or similar clean sans-serif
- **Deployment:** Vercel
- **Blog:** MDX with @next/mdx or contentlayer (local Markdown files in /content/blog/)
- **Email:** ConvertKit API for newsletter signups
- **Booking:** Cal.com or Calendly embed component

---

## DESIGN SYSTEM

### Brand Colors (use these exact values)

```typescript
// tailwind.config.ts — extend colors
colors: {
  navy: '#1B2A4A',      // Primary — headers, nav, footer, dark sections
  slate: '#3D4F6F',     // Secondary text, subtle backgrounds
  gold: '#C8963E',      // Accent — CTAs, highlights, trust badges, hover states
  offwhite: '#F8F6F2',  // Page backgrounds
  charcoal: '#2D2D2D',  // Body text
}
```

### Design Principles

- **Clean and modern.** Think high-end financial services, not flashy mortgage broker.
- **Navy + gold palette.** Navy conveys trust. Gold conveys warmth and quality. No red.
- **Generous whitespace.** Let the content breathe. Don't cram sections together.
- **Typography hierarchy:** Clear distinction between H1, H2, H3, body. H1 should feel authoritative.
- **Cards with subtle shadows** for content sections, not flat boxes.
- **Rounded corners** (rounded-lg or rounded-xl) on cards and buttons — feels approachable.
- **Gold CTAs on navy backgrounds. Navy CTAs on light backgrounds.** High contrast always.
- **No stock photos.** Use Jacob's actual photos (see Photo Assets below). Use subtle gradient overlays or geometric patterns for visual interest where needed.
- **Mobile-first.** Design for 375px width first, then scale up. Every element must look perfect on phone.

### Typography

```
Headings: font-semibold or font-bold, text-navy
  H1: text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl
  H2: text-3xl md:text-4xl
  H3: text-xl md:text-2xl
  
Body: text-base md:text-lg, text-charcoal, leading-relaxed

Small/meta: text-sm, text-slate
```

### Buttons

```
Primary CTA: bg-gold text-white hover:bg-gold/90 rounded-lg px-6 py-3 font-semibold
Secondary CTA: border-2 border-navy text-navy hover:bg-navy hover:text-white rounded-lg px-6 py-3
Ghost: text-gold hover:underline font-medium
```

### Component Patterns

- **Section padding:** py-16 md:py-24 px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8
- **Max container width:** max-w-7xl mx-auto
- **Section alternating backgrounds:** white → offwhite → white → navy (dark section) → white
- **Cards:** bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 md:p-8
- **Trust badges / stat counters:** Grid of 3-4 items with icon + number + label

