## PAGE-BY-PAGE SPECIFICATIONS

### GLOBAL LAYOUT (app/layout.tsx)

**Header / Navigation:**
- Sticky on scroll, white background with subtle shadow when scrolled
- Left: Logo text "Jacob Shope" in navy, font-bold text-xl. Below or beside it in small text: "Mortgage Loan Officer | NMLS# 2090979"
- Center/Right: Nav links — Home, About, Loan Programs (dropdown), Calculators (dropdown), Rates, Blog, Contact
- Far right: Gold CTA button "Get a Free Quote" → links to /contact
- Mobile: Hamburger menu with slide-out drawer. Keep "Get a Free Quote" button visible on mobile header.
- Mobile: Add click-to-call phone icon in header

**Footer:**
- Navy background (#1B2A4A), white/gold text
- 4-column grid on desktop, stacked on mobile:
  - Column 1: "Jacob Shope" name, tagline "Serving Charlotte. Building Futures.", brief 2-line description, social links (Instagram: @jlshopeloans, LinkedIn)
  - Column 2: Quick Links — Home, About, Loan Programs, Calculators, Rates, Blog
  - Column 3: Service Areas — Charlotte, Huntersville, Cornelius, Lake Norman, View All
  - Column 4: Contact info — phone (click-to-call), email (shope@mpirefi.com), office location
- Below columns: Newsletter signup form (email input + "Subscribe" button, ConvertKit integration)
- Bottom bar: "© 2026 Jacob Shope | NMLS# 2090979 | Mpire Financial NMLS# 2090979 | Equal Housing Lender" + Equal Housing Lender icon + NMLS Consumer Access link
- Equal Housing Lender logo must appear in footer on EVERY page (compliance requirement)

### HOMEPAGE (app/page.tsx)

**Section 1 — Hero**
- Split layout: Text left (60%), Photo right (40%) on desktop. Stacked on mobile (text first).
- H1: "Serving Charlotte. Building Futures."
- Subtext (p tag, not H2): "I'm Jacob Shope — a captain with the Charlotte Fire Department and a licensed mortgage loan officer. I've built my career around one thing: showing up for my community. Whether I'm leading my crew on a call or helping a family find the right path to homeownership, I bring the same dedication to everything I do."
- Two CTA buttons: "Get a Free Consultation" (gold, primary) + "Explore Loan Options" (navy outline, secondary)
- Right side: `headshot-primary.jpg` — large, rounded-xl, subtle shadow
- Background: offwhite or subtle gradient

**Section 2 — Trust Signals Bar**
- offwhite or light background
- Grid of 4 items, centered:
  - "Captain, Charlotte Fire Dept." + Shield/Badge icon
  - "NMLS# 2090979" + Verified icon
  - "Charlotte Metro & NC Statewide" + MapPin icon
  - "5-Star Rated" + Star icon (or review count when available)
- Keep these compact. Icon + bold text + small description.

**Section 3 — Loan Programs Overview**
- H2: "Find the Right Loan for You"
- Grid of 6-7 cards (3 columns desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile):
  - Each card: Icon + program name + 1-line description + "Learn More →" link
  - Programs: Conventional, FHA, VA, USDA, Jumbo, Refinance, First-Time Buyer
- Each card links to its /loan-programs/[slug] page

**Section 4 — Mortgage Calculator Preview**
- Navy background section (dark, high contrast)
- H2 (white text): "What Can You Afford?"
- Embedded mini payment calculator (simplified: home price + down payment + rate → monthly payment)
- Gold CTA: "Try Our Full Calculator Suite" → /calculators
- This is a teaser — the full calculators live on their own pages

**Section 5 — Why Work With Me**
- H2: "Why Charlotte Families Trust Jacob Shope"
- 3 columns with icons:
  - "Community First" — brief text about serving Charlotte as both firefighter and LO
  - "Wealth Through Homeownership" — text about using real estate as a wealth-building tool
  - "Guidance You Can Trust" — text about transparency, no hidden fees, honest advice
- Keep this section concise — 2-3 sentences per column max.

**Section 6 — Testimonials**
- H2: "What My Clients Say"
- Carousel or grid of 3 testimonial cards (placeholder content for now)
- Each card: Star rating (5 stars), quote text, client first name + last initial, loan type
- If no real testimonials yet, use placeholder structure with a note to replace

**Section 7 — Blog Preview**
- H2: "Mortgage Tips & Charlotte Market Insights"
- Grid of 3 latest blog post cards (title, excerpt, date, read more link)
- Link: "View All Posts →" to /blog

**Section 8 — Final CTA**
- Navy background, centered text
- H2 (white): "Ready to Get Started?"
- Subtext: "Whether you're buying your first home or refinancing, I'm here to help."
- Two buttons: "Book a Free Consultation" (gold) + "Apply Now" (white outline)

### ABOUT PAGE (app/about/page.tsx)

**Section 1 — Hero Banner**
- Full-width `family-field.jpg` as background with navy overlay (opacity 60-70%)
- H1 (white, centered): "Captain Jacob Shope"
- Subtitle: "Charlotte Fire Department Captain · Mortgage Loan Officer · NMLS# 2090979"

**Section 2 — My Story**
- H2: "Same Dedication. Different Uniform."
- Two-column layout: Text left, `dress-uniform.jpg` right
- Text content (2-3 paragraphs):
  - Paragraph 1: How he got into firefighting, what it means to serve Charlotte, the role of captain
  - Paragraph 2: How he got into mortgage — the connection between protecting families and helping them build wealth through homeownership
  - Paragraph 3: His personal mission — using real estate as a tool for generational wealth, serving the Charlotte community in two ways
- Tone: Confident, grounded, warm. NOT salesy. Written in first person.

**Section 3 — Family**
- Casual section with `couple-sunset.jpg` or `family-station.jpg`
- Brief text about his family, living in the Charlotte/Huntersville area, being a local
- This section is about connection, not selling

**Section 4 — Credentials & Trust**
- Grid or list:
  - NMLS# 2090979
  - Licensed in North Carolina
  - Mpire Financial (company NMLS#)
  - Captain, Charlotte Fire Department
  - Years of experience (placeholder until confirmed)
- Link to NMLS Consumer Access

**Section 5 — CTA**
- "Let's Talk About Your Goals" + Book a Consultation button + Contact button

### LOAN PROGRAM PAGES (app/loan-programs/[slug]/page.tsx)

Use a shared template component. Each page has:
- H1: "[Program Name] in Charlotte, NC"
- Hero section with brief description
- "Key Benefits" section (3-4 bullet points in a styled list or grid)
- "Requirements" section (credit score, down payment, DTI, eligibility)
- "How It Works" — 3-4 step process with numbered icons
- FAQ section at bottom (3-5 questions) — MUST include FAQPage JSON-LD schema
- CTA: "See If You Qualify" → /contact or /apply
- Sidebar or bottom section: Related calculators, link to rates page
- Internal links to other loan programs ("Not sure which loan is right? Compare options →")

Generate unique, substantive content for each program. Do NOT use placeholder "Lorem ipsum" text. Write real mortgage content optimized for Charlotte NC keywords.

### CALCULATOR PAGES (app/calculators/[slug]/page.tsx)

**Payment Calculator (/calculators/payment)**
- Inputs: Home price (slider + input), Down payment ($ and %, linked), Loan term (15/20/30yr toggle), Interest rate, Annual property tax, Annual homeowner's insurance, Monthly PMI (auto-calculate based on down payment < 20%), Monthly HOA
- Output: Total monthly payment (PITI + PMI + HOA), interactive Recharts pie chart showing breakdown by category
- Use sliders for mobile-friendly UX on home price and down payment
- Format all currency with commas and $ signs
- Recalculate on every input change (no submit button)

**Affordability Calculator (/calculators/affordability)**
- Inputs: Annual gross income, Monthly debt payments, Down payment available, Interest rate, Loan term
- Output: Maximum home price (based on 43% DTI), Comfortable home price (based on 36% DTI), Estimated monthly payment at each level
- Visual: Bar chart or gauge showing the range
- Include explanation of DTI ratio

**Refinance Calculator (/calculators/refinance)**
- Inputs: Current loan balance, Current interest rate, Current monthly payment, New interest rate, New loan term, Estimated closing costs
- Output: New monthly payment, Monthly savings, Break-even month, Total interest saved over life of loan
- Visual: Line chart showing cumulative savings over time

**Amortization Schedule (/calculators/amortization)**
- Inputs: Loan amount, Interest rate, Loan term
- Output: Full monthly payment schedule table (month, payment, principal, interest, balance)
- Visual: Area chart showing principal vs interest over time
- Optional: Extra payment input to show payoff acceleration
- Table should be scrollable on mobile with sticky headers

**All calculators must:**
- Be fully client-side (no API calls — instant calculation)
- Use "use client" directive
- Be responsive and touch-friendly
- Use brand colors in charts (navy for primary data, gold for highlights, slate for secondary)
- Include a CTA below results: "Get Your Personalized Rate" → /contact
- Include SEO meta title and description targeting calculator keywords

### BLOG (app/blog/)

**Blog listing page (app/blog/page.tsx):**
- H1: "Mortgage Tips & Charlotte Market Insights"
- Grid of blog post cards (2 columns desktop, 1 mobile)
- Each card: Featured image (or placeholder gradient), title, excerpt (first 160 chars), date, category tag, "Read More →"
- Pagination or "Load More" if more than 12 posts

**Blog post page (app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx):**
- Article layout: max-w-3xl centered
- H1: Post title
- Meta: Date, estimated read time, category
- Author bio at bottom: headshot-primary.jpg, "Jacob Shope is a Charlotte Fire Department captain and mortgage loan officer helping families across the Charlotte metro build wealth through homeownership." + link to /about
- Related posts section (2-3 posts)
- CTA section: "Have questions? Book a free consultation" → /book
- Schema: Article JSON-LD with author, datePublished, headline, image

**MDX blog post structure (/content/blog/example-post.mdx):**
```mdx
---
title: "Step-by-Step Guide to Buying a Home in Charlotte, NC"
description: "Everything you need to know about buying a home in the Charlotte metro area, from pre-approval to closing day."
date: "2026-03-01"
category: "Buying Guides"
image: "/images/blog/charlotte-homes.jpg"
---

Content goes here in standard Markdown...
```

### SERVICE AREA PAGES (app/service-areas/[slug]/page.tsx)

Use a shared template. Each page includes:
- H1: "Mortgage Lender in [City], NC" (or "Lake Norman Mortgage Lender")
- Hero with Google Maps embed centered on that area
- Section: "[City] Housing Market Overview" — local stats, trends, neighborhood descriptions
- Section: "Loan Programs Available in [City]" — links to each loan program
- Section: "Why Choose a Local Mortgage Professional" — community trust angle
- Testimonials from clients in that area (placeholder for now)
- FAQ section with local questions (e.g., "What is the average home price in Huntersville?")
- CTA: "Get Pre-Approved for a Home in [City]" → /contact
- Internal links to other nearby service areas
- UNIQUE content per page — do NOT duplicate content across service area pages

### FAQ PAGE (app/faq/page.tsx)

- H1: "Frequently Asked Mortgage Questions"
- Accordion-style Q&A (use shadcn/ui Accordion component)
- Minimum 15-20 questions covering:
  - Pre-approval process
  - Down payment requirements
  - Credit score requirements
  - FHA vs Conventional
  - Closing costs
  - Refinancing
  - First-time buyer programs in NC
  - NCHFA programs
  - Mortgage rates
  - Timeline to close
  - Documents needed
  - PMI
  - DTI ratio
  - VA loan eligibility
  - USDA eligibility near Charlotte
- MUST include FAQPage JSON-LD schema for every Q&A pair
- Each answer should be substantive (2-4 sentences), not one-liners
- Internal links within answers to relevant pages (e.g., "Learn more about FHA loans →")

### CONTACT PAGE (app/contact/page.tsx)

- H1: "Get in Touch"
- Two-column layout: Form left, contact info + map right
- Form fields: First name, Last name, Email, Phone, Loan type (dropdown: Purchase, Refinance, Not Sure), Purchase timeline (dropdown: ASAP, 1-3 months, 3-6 months, 6+ months, Just exploring), Message (textarea)
- Form submission: Server action → sends email via Resend or Formspree
- Success state: "Thank you! I'll be in touch within 24 hours."
- Right column: Phone (click-to-call link), Email (mailto link), Office address, Google Maps embed, "Book a Consultation" button → /book
- Include Cloudflare Turnstile for spam protection

### RATES PAGE (app/rates/page.tsx)

- H1: "Today's Mortgage Rates in Charlotte, NC"
- Table or card grid showing:
  - 30-Year Fixed
  - 15-Year Fixed
  - FHA 30-Year
  - VA 30-Year
  - 5/1 ARM
- Each row: Loan type, Rate %, APR %, monthly payment per $100K
- "Last Updated: [date]" timestamp
- Store rates in a simple JSON file (/data/rates.json) so Jacob can update easily
- Disclaimer text below: "Rates shown are for informational purposes only and are subject to change without notice. Your actual rate will depend on your credit score, loan amount, down payment, and other factors. Contact me for a personalized rate quote."
- CTA: "Get Your Personalized Rate" → /contact

